title: Bug 4121: JarExporter causes out of Sync (1GILQD5)
description: JarExporter causes out of Sync. When exporting a jar file, it includes itself, resulting in an out of sync state.
OB: When exporting a jar file using the JarExporter, the exported jar file includes itself, leading to an out of sync state. This means that the exported jar file is different from the expected contents.
EB: The exported jar file should not include itself and should only include the relevant files and dependencies necessary for the functionality of the software.
SR:
To reproduce the issue:
1. Open the software.
2. Go to the Export menu.
3. Select the 'Export Jar' option.
4. Follow the export process.
5. Check the exported jar file and verify if it includes itself.
